&nbsp;
1Plaque reduction after surrogate flossing.&nbsp;Data on File: McNeil-PPC, Inc. 2003.

Disposable prophy angles with an innovative new Splatter Guard wiper device engineered to significantly reduce splatter by decreasing the buildup of paste and saliva on the prophy cup.
The spiral ridges on the inside and outside of these latex-free Elite-style cups provide exceptional stain removal and better interproximal cleaning. The prophy angle body features a rounded head for greater clearance and maneuverability in the mouth, plus a slimmer neck design for superior visibility and access.
&nbsp;
"The splatter Guard is my favorite prophy cup, EVER. I feel that I can remove more bacteria without using a higher grit paste or applying too much pressure to the tooth. I wear black overcoats and it typically highlights the splatter. There is no splatter on my shield or overcoat "
Amber Auger, RDH, MHPAmber is a national speaker, writer and blogger for RDH Magazine and the host of #AskAmberRDH, a weekly Facebook live event.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
